    <text id="F8003T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McPherson begins his Congressional campaign and asks for Cameron's support.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
              

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1858-08-26"><abbr expan="August">Ag.</abbr>
                            26/<unclear>58</unclear></date>
                        <name type="place">Gettysburg.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>As you have <unclear>observed</unclear> I have been nominated; and I will next
                    week begin the campaign in Earnest. I have an appointment in Bedford next week,
                    (their Court), &amp; will go then to Mifflintown, <abbr expan="September"
                        >Sept.</abbr> 6.- I wanted to go to <abbr expan="Harrisburg">Harrisbg</abbr>
                    to see you before reading the latter point, but cannot do so in consequence of
                    the engagement in Bedford, which was made without consultation, and which I
                    cannot break. From all quarters I hear <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> from
                        Juniata--<unclear>although</unclear> I knew something of the facts upon
                    which the favorable opinion in based--I hope to stop in H. on my way from
                    Juniata, the latter part of that week, &amp; will be glad to have a talk
                    with you in relation to this <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>, which I believe it is within our
                    power to carry, with proper effort.-</p>
                <p>I <unclear>regret</unclear> not be <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> able to<pb n="2"/>write my
                    place more definitely, but I will be in H, Earlier or later in the week,
                    according as I am detained in Juniata. <unclear>Probably</unclear>, I will not
                    be needed there, the whole week.</p>
                <p>If you have any special personal friends in the District any the lukewarm in the
                    Democrats, I will be gratified if you exert what influence you have over them in
                    my favor,-It will give me great pleasure to remember the kindness, &amp; to
                    serve you <hi rend="underline">in kind</hi>.--For we intend that you shall, some
                    day soon be before the people.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline"><abbr expan="Edward">Edwd.</abbr> M. McPherson</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">I thank you for the <unclear>accts</unclear> sent a month
                            <unclear>since</unclear>-</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
